---
import TutorialLayout from '../../../layouts/TutorialLayout.astro';
import TutorialPlayground from '../../../components/TutorialPlayground.astro';
---

<TutorialLayout 
  title="Introduction to Python" 
  description="Learn about Python and its history"
  currentPage={1}
  totalPages={10}
  nextLink="/en/materi/02-hello-world"
>
  <!-- Preload Pyodide for better performance -->
  <script>
    // Preload Pyodide when user shows intent to use playground
    document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
      // Preload on hover or focus of playground area
      const playground = document.querySelector('[data-playground]');
      if (playground) {
        const preload = () => {
          import('/src/lib/pyodide-runtime.js').then(({ preloadPyodide }) => {
            preloadPyodide();
          });
        };
        
        playground.addEventListener('mouseenter', preload, { once: true });
        playground.addEventListener('focusin', preload, { once: true });
      }
    });
  </script>

  <div slot="content">
    <h1>Introduction to Python</h1>
    
    <p>Welcome to the world of Python programming! Let's start by learning what Python is and who created it.</p>
    <figure>
      <img
        src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/c/c3/Python-logo-notext.svg"
        alt="Python logo"
        loading="lazy"
        style="max-width: 250px; height: 250px;"
      />
      <figcaption>
        Python logo 
        <a
          href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Python-logo-notext.svg"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener"
        >
          Wikimedia Commons
        </a>
      </figcaption>
    </figure>
    
    <h2>What is Python?</h2>
    
    <p>Python is a programming language that is:</p>
    
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Easy to learn</strong> - Simple and readable syntax</li>
      <li><strong>Versatile</strong> - Can be used for web, data science, AI, machine learning, and more</li>
      <li><strong>Powerful</strong> - Has a large ecosystem and widely supported library</li>
      <li><strong>Open Source</strong> - Free and developed by a global community</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h2>Who is the Creator?</h2>
      <figure>
        <img
            src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6b/Guido_van_Rossum_in_PyConUS24_%28cropped%29.jpg/500px-Guido_van_Rossum_in_PyConUS24_%28cropped%29.jpg"
            alt=" at PyCon US 2024"
            loading="lazy"
            style="max-width:60%; height:auto;"
        />
        <figcaption>
            Guido van Rossum speaking at PyCon US 2024 —
            <a href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Guido_van_Rossum_in_PyConUS24_(cropped).jpg" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
            Wikimedia Commons
            </a>, CC BY-SA
        </figcaption>
      </figure>
    <p>Python was created by <strong>Guido van Rossum</strong>, a programmer from the Netherlands. Some interesting facts:</p>
    
    <ul>
      <li>Started developing Python in <strong>1989</strong></li>
      <li>Named "Python" after the TV show "Monty Python's Flying Circus"</li>
      <li>Guido is known as Benevolent Dictator for Life (BDFL) in the Python community.</li>
      <li>Worked at Google (2005-2012) and Dropbox (2013-2019)</li>
    </ul>
    
    <strong>Guido’s philosophy emphasizes simplicity and readability, values that still define Python today.</strong>
    
    <h2>Why is Python Popular?</h2>
    
    <p>Python became one of the most popular programming languages because:</p>
    
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Readable</strong> - Python code is easy to read like English</li>
      <li><strong>Productive</strong> - Can create programs with less code</li>
      <li><strong>Versatile</strong> - Used for web development, automation, data science, AI and many more</li>
      <li><strong>Community</strong> - Large and supportive community</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div slot="playground" data-playground>
    <TutorialPlayground 
      code={`
print("Welcome!")      

language_name = "Python"
year = 1989
print(f"{language_name} was created in {year}")
`}
    />
  </div>
</TutorialLayout>